com.ibm.team.workitem.common

Interface IAuditableCommon

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAuditableClient

    public interface IAuditableCommon
    The auditable library provides access to IAuditables as an interface available on both the client and the server. On the client it can be obtained as a client library, on the server as a service.

    See ITeamRepository and IProcessClientService for documentation on operations that are forwarded to on the client side.

    Since:
    0.5
    See Also:
    IAuditable, ItemProfile

      • getItemQueryIterator

        <T extends IItemHandle> QueryIterator<T> getItemQueryIterator(IItemQuery itemQuery,
                                                            java.lang.Object[] parameters,
                                                            UUID[] contextIds,
                                                            QueryIterator.ReadMode readMode)
        Creates an iterator on a item query result. The item query is evaluated on the first access (next or hasNext). The QueryIterator must be closed after usage.
        Parameters:
        itemQuery - The query to run
        parameters - The query parameters or null if the query does not require any parameters
        contextIds - The contextIds The access context IDs or null to run the query with the default access context.
        readMode - TODO
        readMode - The read mode (committed or uncommitted) to run the query in or null to run the query in the default run mode (committed). Note that in uncommitted mode, the passed context ids are ignored.
        Since:
        4.0.4

        Creates an iterator on a data query result. The query is evaluated on the first access (next or hasNext). The QueryIterator must be closed after usage.

      • resolveAccessContext

        java.lang.Object resolveAccessContext(UUID contextId,
                                    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
        Resolved the given UUID as an access context. The resulting object is either of type IAccessGroup if the context is configured to an access group, a IProcessArea, if the context is project or team, a IContributor or a UUID, the context is IContext.PUBLIC or unknown.
        Since:
        4.0
